      <div class="resource-desc">Arcade machines, computers, calculators. If it has a CPU, MAME emulates it.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="resource-card">
    <div class="resource-icon">🔧</div>
    <div class="resource-info">
      <div class="resource-title">VICE</div>
      <div class="resource-desc">Commodore emulator. Essential for C64 development.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="resource-card">
    <div class="resource-icon">🔧</div>
    <div class="resource-info">
      <div class="resource-title">Ghidra</div>
      <div class="resource-desc">NSA's reverse engineering suite. Free. Powerful. terrifying.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>🎮 Games That Teach</h2>

  <p>
    These games are more educational than any computer science course I've taken:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>TIS-100</strong> - Programming puzzles in fake assembly</li>
    <li><strong>SpaceChem</strong> - Factory simulation with flow-based programming</li>
    <li><strong>Human Resource Machine</strong> - Simple puzzles that teach memory management</li>
    <li><strong>7 Billion Humans</strong> - Multiworker programming</li>
    <li><strong>Shenzhen I/O</strong> - Circuit design and assembly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📚 Books</h2>

  <div class="resource-card">
    <div class="resource-icon">📕</div>
    <div class="resource-info">
      <div class="resource-title">The Soul of a New Machine</div>
      <div class="resource-desc">Tracy Kidder's account of building a minicomputer. Gripping.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="resource-card">
    <div class="resource-icon">📗</div>
    <div class="resource-info">
      <div class="resource-title">Programmers at Work</div>
      <div class="resource-desc">Interviews from the 80s. Gates, Kildall, DRI, and more.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="resource-card">
    <div class="resource-icon">📘</div>
    <div class="resource-info">
      <div class="resource-title">Hackers: Heroes of the Computer Revolution</div>
      <div class="resource-desc">Steven Levy's history. The original hackers, MIT, Homebrew.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>🗄️ Archives Worth Exploring</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://archive.org/details/software">Internet Archive Software Collection</a> - Thousands of old programs</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.pagetable.com">Pagetable</a> - Chris's deep dives into old tech</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.c64.com">C64.com</a> - The Commodore 64 encyclopedia</li>
    <li><a href="http://www.textfiles.com">Textfiles.com</a> - BBS archives from the 80s and 90s</li>
  </ul>

